[size=140][u]Visible Ware Overview[/u][/size]

Adds a [b]Wares on Visible Stations[/b] tab to the [b]Object List[/b] panel in the map. Lists all wares present at stations currently rendered in the map view, grouped by transport type (Container, Solid, Liquid, Condensate), with total stock, production and consumption per hour, and station count. Each ware row is expandable to a per-station breakdown.

[size=130][u]Features[/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Wares on Visible Stations tab[/b]: A dedicated tab in the Object List panel lists all wares that are stocked, produced, or consumed at stations currently visible on the map.
[*] [b]Player and NPC stations[/b]: Both player-owned and NPC stations are included. Player stations always show the full ware breakdown; NPC stations show ware details when the Logical Station Overview visibility rules allow it.
[*] [b]Grouped by transport type[/b]: Wares are organised under section headers: Container Storage, Solid Storage, Liquid Storage, and Condensate Storage.
[*] [b]Per-ware summary row[/b]: Each ware shows a ware icon with name, total production per hour (green), total consumption per hour (red), total stock across all visible stations, and the number of stations that handle it.
[*] [b]Expandable to per-station detail[/b]: Click the [b]+[/b] button on a ware row to expand it and see a sub-row for each station that handles that ware. The sub-row shows the station name with sector below, per-station production/h, consumption/h, and current stock.
[*] [b]Logical Station Overview button[/b]: Each station sub-row has a button to open the Logical Station Overview for that station.
[*] [b]Expand/collapse all[/b]: A button in the column header row expands or collapses all ware rows at once.
[*] [b]Empty state[/b]: If no ware data is found for the visible stations, a clear message is shown.
[*] [b]Cached data[/b]: Ware and station data are refreshed periodically to avoid redundant lookups every render.
[*] [b]Configurable refresh interval[/b]: The data refresh interval (1-10 ticks, default 3) can be adjusted in [b]Extension options[/b].
[*] [b]Compatible with X4 8.00 and 9.00[/b].
[*] [b]Save-safe[/b]: can be added or removed at any time without affecting saved games.
[/list]
[size=130][u]Limitations[/u][/size]

Because [b]Egosoft rejected[/b] the proposal to expose a [b]C.GetMapRenderedSectors(holomap)[/b] function for retrieving the list of sectors currently rendered on the map, this mod falls back to the vanilla approach and works only with stations visible on screen.
As a result, in most cases the data covers only a [b]limited number[/b] of stations - significantly fewer than the total across all known sectors.

