[size=130][u]Usage[/u][/size]

Open the map and click the [b]Wares on Visible Stations[/b] tab in the Object List panel tab strip. The tab is visible whenever you are on any map view.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-VisibleWareOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/visible_ware_overview_tab.png[/img][/spoiler]

All wares present at stations currently visible on the map are listed, grouped by transport type.

[size=125][u]Ware row[/u][/size]

Each ware row contains:
[list]
[*] [b]+/-[/b] expand button on the left to reveal per-station detail.
[*] Ware icon and name.
[*] Total production per hour (shown in green).
[*] Total consumption per hour (shown in red).
[*] Total stock across all visible stations handling this ware.
[*] Number of visible stations handling this ware.
[/list]
[size=125][u]Station sub-row[/u][/size]

Click [b]+[/b] on a ware row to expand it. Each station that handles the ware gets a sub-row:
[list]
[*] Station name with sector shown below it.
[*] Per-station production per hour (green) and consumption per hour (red).
[*] Current stock at that station.
[*] [b]Logical Station Overview[/b] button to open the station inventory and build plan.
[/list]
[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-VisibleWareOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/visible_ware_overview_stations.png[/img][/spoiler]

[size=125][u]Column headers and expand/collapse all[/u][/size]

The [b]+/-[/b] button in the column header row expands or collapses all ware rows simultaneously.

[size=125][u]Extension options[/u][/size]

[b]Options Menu > Extension options > Visible Ware Overview[/b]:
[list]
[*] [b]Data refresh interval[/b] (1-10, default 3): Number of UI ticks between data refreshes. Lower values keep ware data more up to date; higher values reduce CPU usage.
[*] [b]Debug level[/b]: Sets the verbosity of debug logging (None / Debug / Trace). Intended for troubleshooting.
[/list]
[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-VisibleWareOverview/refs/heads/main/docs/images/options.png[/img][/spoiler]

